html.body: CYCLIN B module The last cyclin intervening in the cycle controls entry and exit of mitosis. CycB1/CDC2 activates the G2/M transition. The complex is inactivated by the protein kinase PKMYT1 (PMID:9001210; PMID:12697828; PMID:12814430). The dephosphorylation and activation of the CDK complex is controlled by the phosphatase CDC25C (PMID:12814430). The phosphorylation and inactivation of the CycB1/CDC2 complex is insured by the WEE1 and the dephosphorylation and activation by CDC25C (PMID:8348613). For full activation, CycB1/CDC2 phosphorylation by CAK (CycH/CDK7/MNAT1) is required (PMID:12459251).
